meta-openstack
===================

This layer provides support for building the packages from the OpenStack project.
The layer contains recipes for the nova, glance, keystone, cinder, quantum, swift
and horizon components.

Dependencies
------------

This layer depends on:

URI: git://github.com/openembedded/oe-core.git
branch: master
tag: yocto-1.4.1

URI: git://github.com/openembedded/meta-oe.git
branch: dylan
revision: HEAD
patches: 0001-python-sqlalchemy-update-to-0.7.9.patch
layers: meta-oe
	meta-networking
    meta-ruby

URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-virtualization
branch: master
revision: 7040db74c375ef55d1b040f53071be29590882de
patches: 0001-linux-yocto-Added-3.8-kernel-bbappend.patch

The patches for the layers can be found in the patches folder. They can be
applied using git am.

Maintenance
-----------

Maintainers: Mihai Prica <prica.mihai@gmail.com>

License
-------

All metadata is MIT licensed unless otherwise stated. Source code included
in tree for individual recipes is under the LICENSE stated in each recipe
(.bb file) unless otherwise stated.

Target images
-------------

There are two target images: nova-image-compute and nova-image-controller.
This contain the packagegroups with the same name and can be used to create
the two types of targets. There are no extra configurations required to build
these images.

